SIMPLE: turnstile
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Turnstile
<hw>Turn"stile`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
revolving frame in a footpath, preventing the passage of horses or
cattle, but admitting that of persons; a turnpike. See
<er>Turnpike</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 1.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A similar arrangement for registering the number of
persons passing through a gateway, doorway, or the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Turnstone</ent>⟦br⟧
